bug.short_desc: The mobile password field does not work properly on Android

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1055 screenshot that displays the error
If a password field (qx.ui.mobile.form.PasswordField) is focused on an android phone it seems like the field is cloned and displayed with an offset (see screenshot).
- it works well in the chrome browser. - it is reproducible in the android browser with the qooxdoo playground

Thanks for the bug report.
This should be a duplicate of bug 5341. The bug is unfortunately a bug in combination with iScroll (and the css3 styles which are set by it - so actually it is an Android browser bug). You should disable iScroll for Android, when you want to use qooxdoo mobile with it. Sorry, that I can not help you right now. I will have a look on the bug pretty soon.
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 5341 ***
